ceptors in this age group. 5. The functional maturation of GABAA and GABAB receptors was studied using focal applications of GABA to the soma and the apical dendrite. Somatic GABA applications to adult neurons held at depolarized membrane potentials evoked a triphasic response, consisting of 1) a GABAA-mediated hyperpolarizing fast component (GABAhf; reversal potential, -76 mV), 2) a GABAA-mediated depolarizing phase (GABAd; -54 mV), and 3) a hyperpolarizing late response (GABAhl; -80 mV). The GABAd response could be demonstrated at all ages in almost every neuron.},
